{"calories":"860","carbs":92,"category":{"badge_name":"","display_name":"Dinner","display_order":1,"is_filterable":false,"insight_segment_slug":"main-recipe-ratings","slug":"main"},"choices_available":[],"description":"We like to think that there’s no sandwich we haven’t tried, so we bring you our latest obsession: the \u003ci\u003epiadina\u003c/i\u003e. This classic Roman dish pairs thin, crispy flatbread with any number of delicious fillings. Here, we’re sticking to the Italian theme, by sandwiching tomatoes, basil, and Asiago and mozzarella cheeses into crunchy grilled pizza crust. For a side of greenery, we bring you a grilled onion and arugula salad. Grilled sandies for the win!","difficulty":"medium","external_id":"0d2818a44d","fat":39,"images":[{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24033/2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_MOBILE.jpg","size":"full","type":"portrait"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24030/2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"full","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24030/hero_2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"hero","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24030/menu_small_2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"medium-rectangle","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24030/small_square_2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"small-square","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24030/medium_square_2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"medium-square","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24030/recipe_profile_page_2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_HERO.jpg","size":"large-rectangle","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24036/2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_THUMB.jpg","size":"full","type":"card"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/24036/menu_small_2662_Tomato_and_Mozzarella_Piadina_with_Basil_and_Arugula_Salad_THUMB.jpg","size":"medium-rectangle","type":"card"}},{"image":{"url":"/assets/blank_profile-62376be1ebee267193d25c20f8cd8bc5a6c47743a4a323d32a54ecdf231b7b80.png","size":"large_cropped","type":"main_cropped"}}],"name":"Tomato and Mozzarella Piadina with Basil and Arugula Salad","novice_time":null,"portion_count":2,"prep_time":"30-40","pro_time":null,"product_type":{"slug":"subscription","included_in_subscription":true},"protein":30,"public_slug":"grilled-caprese-piadina-with-baby-greens-3","pdf_url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/public_uploads/recipe/region_schedule/downloadable_recipe_card/13919/recipe_card20170626-4-1nh4we6.pdf","recipe_id":2662,"type":"regular","servings":2,"short_name":"Tomato and Mozzarella Piadina","subtitle":"with Basil and Arugula Salad","title":"Tomato and Mozzarella Piadina","legal_copy_short":null,"available_for_non_sub":false,"additional_price":"0","cooking_tip":"\u003cp\u003eBe sure to read through the entire recipe before you begin cooking.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cp\u003eNo outdoor grill? Preheat a grill pan in Step 3. Or, preheat oven to 425ºF. Rub olive oil on a baking sheet, carefully add dough, and rub 1 tablespoon olive oil on top. Bake until crisp and lightly browned, 12-15 minutes. Add garlic, half of basil, Asiago, and mozzarella. Return to oven to melt cheese, about 3 minutes more. Skip cooking the onion, and thinly slice as much as desired for your salad.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhen you roll it out, pizza dough tends to shrink back. Keep going! If you have trouble, let it temper at room temperature for 5 minutes.\u003c/p\u003e","equipment":["grill or grill pan","rolling pin (optional)"],"id":2662,"ingredients":["fresh mozzarella","tomatoes","basil","lemon","garlic","red onion","balsamic vinegar","flour","pizza dough","shredded Asiago cheese","balsamic glaze","baby arugula"],"ingredients_full":[{"name":"fresh mozzarella","quantity":"4.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":1,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1093/medium_square_fresh_mozzarella.jpg"},{"name":"tomatoes","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":2,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1376/medium_square_medium_square_tomato-2-new.jpg"},{"name":"basil","quantity":"0.5","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":3,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1275/medium_square_medium_square_basil-test.jpg"},{"name":"lemon","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":4,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/16/medium_square_LEMON_SLICED_1_copy.jpg"},{"name":"garlic","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"clove","displayOrder":5,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/2/medium_square_GARLIC_PEELED_copy.jpg"},{"name":"red onion","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":6,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/90/medium_square_red-onion-cut-half.jpg"},{"name":"balsamic vinegar","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":7,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/3/medium_square_BALSAMIC_VINEGAR0019.jpg"},{"name":"flour","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":8,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/285/medium_square_FLOUR_copy.jpg"},{"name":"pizza dough","quantity":"12.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":9,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1609/medium_square_medium_square_medium_square_pizza-dough.jpg"},{"name":"shredded Asiago cheese","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":10,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1960/medium_square_shredded-cheese-asiago.jpg"},{"name":"balsamic glaze","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"packet","displayOrder":11,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1485/medium_square_balsamic_glaze.jpg"},{"name":"baby arugula","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":12,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/239/medium_square_arugula-test.jpg"}],"is_tastemaker":false,"upgradeable":false,"is_holiday_hack":false,"pantry_items":["olive oil","kosher salt","black pepper"],"pantry_items_full":[{"name":"olive oil","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":13,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/267/medium_square_olive-oil-test.jpg"},{"name":"kosher salt","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":14,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/473/medium_square_kosher-salt.jpg"},{"name":"black pepper","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":15,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/493/medium_square_spice-black-pepper-test.jpg"}],"steps":[{"title":" Prepare Ingredients","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22197/recipe_card_size_1._Prepare_2X.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003ePreheat grill to medium heat (see Recipe Tip). Rinse all produce. Cut \u003cstrong\u003emozzarella\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003etomatoes\u003c/strong\u003e into .25-inch slices. Roughly chop \u003cstrong\u003ebasil \u003c/strong\u003eleaves, discarding stems. Halve\u003cstrong\u003e lemon\u003c/strong\u003e. Mince \u003cstrong\u003egarlic\u003c/strong\u003e. Peel \u003cstrong\u003eonion\u003c/strong\u003e and slice into .25-inch rings, being careful not to separate layers—they're easier to grill in 1 piece.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":" Make Dressing and Roll Out Dough","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22198/recipe_card_size_2._Roll_out_Dough.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eIn a medium bowl, whisk together \u003cstrong\u003ebalsamic\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003evinegar\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e1 squeeze lemon juice\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e2 tablespoons olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003epepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired to combine. Set dressing aside, and save remaining lemon for another use. Sprinkle \u003cstrong\u003eflour\u003c/strong\u003e onto a clean, dry surface. Using a rolling pin or the heels of your hands, roll and stretch\u003cstrong\u003e dough \u003c/strong\u003einto a rectangular shape, about .5-inch thick (see Recipe Tip).\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Grill Onions","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22199/recipe_card_size_3._Grill_Onion.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eIf using a grill pan, place it over medium heat now. Rub\u003cstrong\u003e onion rings\u003c/strong\u003e on both sides with\u003cstrong\u003e .5 tablespoon olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e,\u003cstrong\u003e \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003epepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired, keeping layers intact. When grill is just smoking, add \u003cstrong\u003eonion\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003erings\u003c/strong\u003e in a single layer and cook until charred and softened, 3 minutes per side. Remove from grill, roughly chop, and add to bowl with dressing.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":" Grill Flatbread","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22200/recipe_card_size_4._Grill_Dough.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eRub \u003cstrong\u003e.5 tablespoon olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e all over \u003cstrong\u003epizza dough\u003c/strong\u003e. Transfer\u003cstrong\u003e dough\u003c/strong\u003e to grill and cook until golden on bottom, about 2 minutes. Carefully flip, then sprinkle over \u003cstrong\u003egarlic\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003ehalf of\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003ebasil\u003c/strong\u003e. Layer\u003cstrong\u003e Asiago \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003emozzarella\u003c/strong\u003e cheeses on top and continue grilling until cheese is melted and flatbread is charred and cooked through, about 2 minutes more.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Finish Piadina","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22201/recipe_card_size_5._Finish_Dough.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eRemove \u003cstrong\u003eflatbread\u003c/strong\u003e from grill and halve crosswise. Layer 1 half\u003cstrong\u003e \u003c/strong\u003ewith \u003cstrong\u003etomatoes\u003c/strong\u003e and drizzle over \u003cstrong\u003ebalsamic glaze\u003c/strong\u003e. Top with other half of flatbread, cheese-side down, to close piadina.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Plate Piadina","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/22202/recipe_card_size_6._Plate.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eQuarter \u003cstrong\u003epiadina\u003c/strong\u003e (each person gets 2 pieces). Add \u003cstrong\u003earugula \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003eremaining basil \u003c/strong\u003eto bowl with grilled onions and dressing, and toss everything to coat. Serve \u003cstrong\u003etomato and mozzarella\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003epiadina\u003c/strong\u003e with \u003cstrong\u003earugula salad\u003c/strong\u003e, and dig in!\u003c/p\u003e"}],"tags":{"all":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"For the grill","slug":"for-the-grill","hex_color":""}],"allergens":[{"name":"Soy","slug":"soy","hex_color":""},{"name":"Milk","slug":"milk","hex_color":""},{"name":"Wheat","slug":"wheat","hex_color":""}],"proteins":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"Bread","slug":"bread","hex_color":""}],"publicFacing":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"For the grill","slug":"for-the-grill","hex_color":""}],"feature":[]}}